n>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>....]ΗΣΑΤΟΑΥΤΟ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΠΑΝΤΑΤ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΥΤΑΟΥΝΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΓΙΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.1 Ῥ\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003291_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003291_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003291.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003291-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>lapis: ΙΟΥΦΙΝ; Korhonen: ουφῖν[αν]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: ζήσα[ς]; Pleket: ζήσα[σαν]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: [ἠγορ]ήσατο\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Korhonen reads a Σ, but it could also be a Ο\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Korhonen reads a Γ, but it could also be a T\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>…my mother Rouphinan … Hesychios, while alive, purchased … all …\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>… mia madre Rouphinan … Hesychios, mentre era vivo, acquistò … tutto …\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph must have been partly metrical (ll. 1-2), as Korhonen pointed out. It can be assumed that Hesychios had acquired the burial place while alive (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζήσας\u003C/span>) for his mother Rouphina (for himself and another deceased (?): \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αὐτοῖς\u003C/span>). At l. 4 a supplement could be \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">[πάντα τ]ὸν χρόνον\u003C/span> to indicate the permanent possession of the purchase of the tomb or with \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">[πάντα τ]ὸν τόπον\u003C/span> to indicate the purchase of the entire place for the burial of the deceased. The names Rouphina and Hesychios recur in Christian epitaphs from Syracuse, see SEG 36.872 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002932\" target=\"_blank\">ISic002932\u003C/a>, IG 14.164 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000985\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000985\u003C/a>, Agnello 1950: 60 no.11 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002918\" target=\"_blank\">ISic002918\u003C/a>. \u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 2004.0655 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 54.0910 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 194 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[178,181,184,187,189,192,195],{"id":179,"html":180},"editions","\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al0-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> μητ]έρα μου &lt;Ῥ&gt;ουφῖνα̣[ν \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] Ἡσύχιος · ζήσα[ς \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> ἠγορ]ήσατο αὐτο[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] πάντα τ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]υτα οὖν Σ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΓΙΑ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.1 Ῥ\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al0-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>...]ΕΡΑΜΟΥIΟΥΦΙΝ.[.\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΗΣΥΧΙΟΣ·ΖΗΣΑ[.\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>....]ΗΣΑΤΟΑΥΤΟ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΠΑΝΤΑΤ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΥΤΑΟΥΝΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΓΙΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.1 Ῥ\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":182,"html":183},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>lapis: ΙΟΥΦΙΝ; Korhonen: ουφῖν[αν]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: ζήσα[ς]; Pleket: ζήσα[σαν]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: [ἠγορ]ήσατο\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Korhonen reads a Σ, but it could also be a Ο\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Korhonen reads a Γ, but it could also be a T\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":185,"html":186},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>…my mother Rouphinan … Hesychios, while alive, purchased … all …\u003C/p>  ",{"id":185,"html":188},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>… mia madre Rouphinan … Hesychios, mentre era vivo, acquistò … tutto …\u003C/p>  ",{"id":190,"html":191},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph must have been partly metrical (ll. 1-2), as Korhonen pointed out. It can be assumed that Hesychios had acquired the burial place while alive (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζήσας\u003C/span>) for his mother Rouphina (for himself and another deceased (?): \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αὐτοῖς\u003C/span>). At l. 4 a supplement could be \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">[πάντα τ]ὸν χρόνον\u003C/span> to indicate the permanent possession of the purchase of the tomb or with \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">[πάντα τ]ὸν τόπον\u003C/span> to indicate the purchase of the entire place for the burial of the deceased. The names Rouphina and Hesychios recur in Christian epitaphs from Syracuse, see SEG 36.872 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002932\" target=\"_blank\">ISic002932\u003C/a>, IG 14.164 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000985\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000985\u003C/a>, Agnello 1950: 60 no.11 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002918\" target=\"_blank\">ISic002918\u003C/a>. \u003C/p>  ",{"id":193,"html":194},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 2004.0655 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 54.0910 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 194 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":196,"html":197},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[199,201],{"image":95,"thumb":200,"title":98},"ISic003291_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":202,"thumb":203,"title":98},"ISic003291.jpg","ISic003291-thumb.jpg","\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Epitaph of Rouphina and Hesychios\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t  